cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper is about evaluating session-based recommendation algorithms, which are commonly used in e-commerce and media streaming sites. Therefore, the most likely category is Information Retrieval (cs.IR), which deals with the retrieval of relevant information. Machine learning (cs.LG) is also a likely category, as the paper discusses the performance of different algorithms. Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) is another possible category, as some of the algorithms may involve processing text data. Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) are less likely categories, but they could be relevant if the paper discusses the security or social aspects of recommendation systems.
